    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess whether outdoor activities are effective in preventing
      the development and progression of juvenile-onset myopia in Chinese children.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      1. To determine if increased engagement in outdoor activities reduces the development and
           progression of myopia in Chinese school children.

        2. To identify the risk factors associated with the development and progression of
           juvenile-onset myopia.

        3. To characterize the interaction between refractive error and education.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
